A devastating earthquake with a magnitude of 7.8 hit Sichuan province, causing over 8,700 deaths and widespread destruction.
China allocated 200 million yuan for relief efforts, with international support pouring in from Russia, Germany, Norway, and Belgium.
The ASEAN Inter-Parliamentary Assembly and Vietnam also expressed condolences.
Despite the tragedy, Chinese authorities were unable to predict the earthquake, highlighting the challenges of earthquake forecasting.
The disaster areas face further challenges with heavy rainfall expected, increasing the risk of landslides.
The global community stands in solidarity with China during this difficult time.
